== Biography ==
Anne B Callender was born in Stockton-on-Tees, County Durham in about 1866.  When the 1881 Census was taken on 3 April 1881, she was a 15 year old Farmers Daughter living at Hardwick Field Farm, Darlington Back Lane, Stockton-on-Tees.  Her father is a Butcher and Farmer of 22 acres called [[Callender-692|George Callender]].  Her mother was [[Best-7946|Alice Best]] who had died in 1869 and her father was now married to [[Anderson-83115|Anne Anderson]].<ref>
